# Linking & Sources

Internal links

- Prefer absolute-from-root doc links, e.g., `/series/php-basics/chapters/01-getting-started`.
- Link to colocated code using relative paths.

External links

- Use markdown links with descriptive anchors.
- Cite authoritative sources when appropriate.

GitHub Edit Links

- Configured via `editLink.pattern` to point to the repo edit page for each doc.

License

- Content and code are MIT licensed. Include attribution where appropriate.
